Boil a large #pot{} of salted water from @water{to taste} with @salt{to taste} for the @dried linguine{180%g}.

> If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

When boiling, add the linguine to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until softened, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pot, off the heat. Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and stir through to prevent sticking.

Meanwhile, drain the @grilling cheese{200%g} then cut into 2cm cubes. Place in a #bowl{} of cold water. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve, peel and chop the @onion{2%units} into small pieces. Halve the @bell pepper{1%unit} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Halve the @chilli{1%unit} and discard the core and seeds. Finely chop.

Place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Remove the cheese cubes from the water and pat dry with kitchen paper. Once the pan is hot, fry the grilling cheese until golden all over, turning often, ~{4-5%minutes}. Once cooked, remove from the pan and cover to keep warm.

Return the (now empty) pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Add the pepper and onion and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Cook until softened, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the garlic and @Cajun spice mix{2%sachet} and fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute} more. Pour in the @passata{1%pack}, 100ml water and @sugar{¼%tsp}. Simmer together for ~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir half the @creme fraiche{65%g} into the sauce. Add the cheese and pasta and cook, stirring, until everything is warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season to taste with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and @sugar{to taste}. Roughly chop the @parsley{5%g}(roughly chopped).

Divide hearty helpings of Cajun linguine between bowls. Top with a dollop of creme fraiche and a sprinkling of chopped parsley. Finish off with as much chopped chilli as you like (use less if you don't like spice).